  <h1>
   texture_debug_messages
  </h1>
  This function can be used to enable or disable texture debug messages. When enabled (set to
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  ), additional information about texture page use will be sent to the output window. Set to
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  to disable this output again.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">texture_debug_messages(enable);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      enable
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Boolean
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Enable or disable the texture debug messages
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if global.debug
{
    texture_debug_messages(true);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check the value of a global variable and if it is set to
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  then texture debug messages are enabled.
 </body>
</html>